page.title: 12COLLINGBOURNE WOODS
page.content: The Forestry Commission looks after the forest, which has an area of 1200 acres. A wildlife ranger looks after the wildlife which include a large number of deer. The trees are mainly beech, with spruce larch and other coniferous trees. It is a mixed wood, and there are also some ornamental trees such as cherry.Some of the trees are between 150 and 200 years old although most of them have been planted in the last 50 years. The woods are used regu;arly by the people of the village. A County council byway cuts through the woods and so cars can be taken into the woods.
